dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of railways and five classes of roads are shown.  Covers area west from Rathenow to Neuentempel to the east, and north from Zehdenick to Kloster Zinna to the south. Berlin roughly at center of sheet.  Sheet N.53, Berlin from series issued in various editions by Geographical Section, General Staff, No. 4346.  Cataloging agency's copy has running watermark in lower margin of sheet: Papeterie de Renage (Isère).  IXA.  Military grid.  Nord de Guerre Zone Grid ... Spheroid, Du Plessis..  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Includes legend, Incidence of grid letters diagrams, Convergence for corners of this sheet diagram, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data: Nord de Guerre Grid, Index to adjoining sheets, Index to corresponding sheets of G.S.G.S. 4416, C. Europe 1/100,000, Conversion table, Authorities, and Glossary.
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
